<P>
   DOCKERS-AD-COLUMN _ In a khakis counterattack, Levi Strauss &AMP;
Co. is responding to inroads made by competitors by portraying its
Dockers line of casual pants for men in a far more sensual and
youthful manner. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   NISSAN-ASSESS (Tokyo) _ Once again, the future of Japan's
second-largest car maker, Nissan Motor Co., is uncertain. The
announcement Wednesday by DaimlerChrysler AG that it was walking
away from negotiations about acquiring a controlling stake in
Nissan and in its equally troubled truck-making affiliate, Nissan
Diesel, ended one topic of speculation and debate only to renew
another: What will happen to Nissan? By Stephanie Strom.
