<P>
   These columns for release Friday, March 12, 1999 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Some people say having a father
who was once president gives George W. Bush a big boost. That may
be right, but if Sunday's press conference is any indication,
George W. may spend more time than he really wants answering
questions about his father, George Herbert Walker Bush. We've been
down this road before, but let's go down this road again. The
governor is not a Junior, in any sense. (Arnold Garcia is the
editorial page editor of the Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ One is an insurance defense
attorney from Beaumont. The other helps run a family-owned
construction company in LaPorte, between Houston and Galveston.
Both are married with two children. Together, the two men _
Democrat David Bernsen and Republican Mike Jackson _ make up the
smallest freshman class in the Texas Senate for as long as anyone
can remember. (McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WALKER-COLUMN _ LONGVIEW, Texas _ I watched Monica on television
last week. What a pitiful sight. She has the shape and the polish
of a woman, but she is a girl. Though she seemed not to lack for
material things throughout her life, she definitely missed out on
some intangibles. Nurturing. Self-image. Self-confidence.
Self-worth. (Ana Pecina Walker is managing editor of the Longview
News-Journal). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
