Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-CBC (Montreal) -- The CBC, Canada's innovative national
broadcaster, has for decades been one of the strongest threads
binding the nation. Now labor unrest, budget cuts and the open
hostility of Prime Minister Jean Chretien threaten it. By Colin
Nickerson. 1100 words.
