   NATION
</P>
<P>
   COUNTIES-GROWTH _ Of the nation's 2,426 counties with at least
10,000 people in 1998, four of the top 10 fastest-growing were in
Georgia {Forsyth, Paulding, Dawson and Henry, two each were in
Colorado and Texas, and one each was in Nevada and Virginia. (Soto,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   ATTN: Georgia, Texas, Colorado editors.
</P>
<P>
   TERMITES _ NEW ORLEANS _ This is not your typical tour of the
French Quarter. On Thursday, termite experts take a walking tour of
the 17th and 18th century building being eaten by termites. The
critters are a major problem here - as evidenced by how many tents
you see over homes being fumigated. Experts say all the beautiful
oak trees, not to mention all the houses in the French Quarter
could be ruined if action isn't taken. (Konigsmark, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DORM-CAMPUS-FIRES _ High-rise dormitories at a dozen
universities across Texas don't have sprinkler systems or smoke
detectors, according to the State Fire Marshall's Office. The
inspection was sparked by a dorm fire at Texas Tech in December
1997 and the University of Texas has already been threatened by AFD
concerning safety problems. Many of these universities are now in a
two-year plan to retrofit the buildings _ coming hat in hand to the
Lege for money _ but exactly how safe are students in the meantime?
We talk to students, administrators and local fire officials.
(Shah, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   STATE LEGISLATIVE NEWS
</P>
<P>
   CAPITOL-REPORT _ AUSTIN _ Capitol report. News briefs, bright
moments and other tidbits from the Texas Legislature. (Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
