conservative Sen. Phil Gramm of Texas and liberal Sen. Barbara
Boxer of California _ introduce an alternative to the annual
process whereby the White House certifies which of some 30 nations
are partners in the fight against illegal narcotics. The process,
in effect for 13 years, draws perennial criticism from lawmakers in
both parties. By GARY MARTIN.
