state of emergency in 167 of the 254 Texas counties because of fire
dangers caused by a persistent drought that has extended through an
abnormally dry winter. Bush said Texans need to conserve water,
reduce fire risks and position firefighting equipment and personnel
in areas of danger. By R.G. RATCLIFFE.
