<P>
   FILM-DEEP END &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The real misery comes in sitting through ``The Deep
End of the Ocean,'' which is all over the place. Michelle Pfeiffer
is undeniably the star, and she gets all of her close-ups. But
``Deep End'' is also scrupulous in trying to get everybody's
feelings into the picture. It's so rigidly worked out that it
doesn't seem to be about anything _ it bends over backward in
trying to be fair. Lacking a point of view, the movie is a mawkish
mess, a USA cable movie given the emotional meandering of an
Actor's Studio exercise. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-THE CORRUPTOR &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Even the name of the new action thriller, ``The
Corruptor,'' sounds anemic. This story of cops who initially can't
stand each other when forced together and who learn to trust each
other brings together Chow Yun-Fat, the elegant Hong Kong movie
icon, and Mark Wahlberg, who did a credible job in last year's
``The Big Hit.'' By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-SCHOOL OF FLESH &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ French actress Isabelle Huppert's mystery _ even when
she cries, she's blank-faced _ is the center of director Benoit
Jacquot's new film, ``The School of Flesh.'' Jacquot seems her
equal in terms of enigma. They've created a low-blood-pressure tale
about the dirty magnetism of sex. Huppert plays a French fashion
executive who falls for the slinky young package played by Vincent
Martinez. He's younger and morally pliant _ a hustler who plays on
both sides of the sexual equator. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has
moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-GOD SAID &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In August 1994, former ``Saturday Night Live'' player
Julia Sweeney's life took a sudden downturn: Doctors discovered
that her brotherMike had advanced-stage lymphoma. Mike and
Sweeney's parents moved in with Sweeney during his chemotherapy,
cramping life at her dream house. And in March 1995 _ shortly
before Mike's death _ Sweeney found out that she had ovarian
cancer. From this ``annus horribulus,'' Sweeney developed the
one-woman show, ``God Said, `Ha!''' By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has
moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-LOCK STOCK &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The British noir comedy ``Lock, Stock and Two Smoking
Barrels'' moves at a blur, like it has actually been fired from one
of those smoking barrels. But it misses its target. By ELVIS
MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-THE RAGE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Nominally a sequel to the 1976 Brian De Palma hit
about a shy and telekinetic teen girl, ``The Rage'' is more of a
remake of ``Carrie'' _ and less a remake than a pastiche of the
worst of 1999's other teen movies. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has
moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-WING COMMANDER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Wing Commander'' turns out to be as interesting as
dropping $6.50 in a video game and then standing there staring at
it with your hands in your pockets for an hour and a half. By
ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainmenmt category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
