   JOHNSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Having received a chilly reception from Florida Gov.
Jeb Bush a few weeks ago, Ward Connerly has brought his
anti-affirmative action medicine show to George W. Bush's range.
Connerly, the African-American member of the University of
California board of regents who spearheaded the successful
referendum that terminated affirmative action in that state, came
to Austin to show support for proposed legislation that would
outlaw it in Texas. By CECIL JOHNSON. Story has moved in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
