   BKC-NCAA-LAFAYETTE (Easton, Pa.) _ The three Chinese tattoos
scrolled along Tyson Whitfield's right arm proclaim that he fears
no man. No such announcement is necessary to reveal that shooting a
basketball doesn't bother him, either. By Bob Duffy.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-MIAMI (Coral Gables, Fla.) _ Miami has undergone a
tremendous turnaround, from 0-18 five years ago in the Big East to
a legitimate top 10 team. By Mark Blaudschun.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-TEMPLE (Undated) _ John Chaney is focused on his Temple
team, concerned about the sore hand of guard Quincy Wadley as well
as how to go about beating what he considers a ``well-coached
ballclub which does a tremendous job at (defense)'' in underdog
Kent State. By Nick Cafardo.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-MASON (Undated) _ Don't expect George Evans to be
intimidated by anything Cincinnati tries to throw his way. Somehow
the spector of a full-court press or a double-team isn't quite as
threatening as facing the end. By Peter May.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-CINCINNATI (Undated) _ The Bearcats remain living proof
that, yes, Duke can be beaten, which of course will mean little or
nothing when they play George Mason in the first round of the East
Regional. By Peter May.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-TEXAS (Undated) _ Chris Mihm is a top-notch big man
with a Kevin McHale kind of game and makes the Longhorn game click.
By Michael Vega.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-PURDUE (Undated) _ Gene Keady has been around since the
turn of the century, has never been to a Final 4; has a Jim Boeheim
(can't win when it counts) reputation. By Michael Vega.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-RYAN-COLUMN (Undated) _ The following does not
constitute a major news bulletin: Kent University will not be
winning the national championship this year. Or any other year. By
Bob Ryan.
</P>
