<P>
   COX-CABLE _ America Online makes deals with SBC, Pac Bell,
Southwestern bell and Nevada Bell to offer DSL cable service.This
is the second content deal SBC has made for its high speed DSL
service. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA-ARENA _ Turner Sports &AMP; Entertainment Development Inc.
is providing another look at the progress at Philips Arena today.
The tour will include a first look at team locker rooms, the Hawks'
practice court and other views from the ground floor looking up
toward the arena's roof. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (f) Financial and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   POWERPLANTS _ Two more power plants are being built in Georgia
to boost capacity during the peak summer months. Dynegy announced
plans for a plant near Franklin and Sonat plans its third Georgia
plant, in Upson County. Southern Co. announced its own project in
January. The rush is on to meet growing electricity demand in the
Southeast. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   HOME-REMODELING _ About $8 trillion is invested in America's
homes and, according to the Joint Center for Housing Studies at
Harvard University, the owners are spending $150 billion a year _
or 2 percent of the GDP _ remodeling those homes. Story reports
findings of the 3-year study of remodeling activity. Local adds,
though there are no hard regional data at this time. (Harte,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
