   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-HEAVYWEIGHT-TITLES _ NEW YORK _ The unification of the
heavyweight titles may be just the bandaid boxing needed. The three
major titles haven't been fused since Riddick Bowe renounced the
WBC belt shortly after defeating Evander Holyfield in 1992. Now the
title will finally be unified after Holyfield fights Lennox Lewis
on Saturday at Madison Garden. (Schultz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
