<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX WASHINGTON BUREAU CORRECTION
 &HT;    By RICK CHRISTIE 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ In a story that moved Tues., March 9, for
publication Wed., March 10, the Cox News Service incorrectly
reported that the total of more than 17,000 deaths in Central
America as a result of Hurricane Mitch would equal American losses
during the Korean War based on information from Gen. Charles
Wilhelm, commander-in-chief of the U.S. Southern Command.
</P>
<P>
   While there is some disagreement over the number, the U.S.
Department of Defense figure is 36,914.
</P>
<P>
   The Cox News Service regrets the error.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
