   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, March 12. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
NAVAJO-MEDICINE (Window Rock, Ariz.) - For more than 30 years, Jack
Jackson has warned the Navajo Nation that the number of medicine
men on the nation's largest reservation is dwindling and some
ceremonies are in danger of being lost forever. Now, as the tribe
is in the midst of a pilot program that attracted more than 300
applicants and provides stipends for young Navajos, Jackson and
others are wondering if it's too little, too late. By BILL DONOVAN.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BIGHORN HUNTER (Phoenix) - Arizona businessperson Sherwin Scott has
spent $1.1 million to hunt bighorn sheep. For the second straight
year, the high-rolling but low-profile hunter has paid several
hundred thousand dollars for a shot at killing a world-record
bighorn in the Rocky Mountains. By LISA GONDERINGER. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
