<P>
   CLINTON (Antigua, Guatemala) _ President Clinton vigorously
denied that the administration had minimized evidence of nuclear
spying by China and defended his policy of engagement with Beijing
as the only effective means of restraining Chinese behavior. By
John M. Broder.
