intensified between the scientific value of sharing information and
the national security need to keep secrets _ including advanced
designs of nuclear weapons. Scientists and engineers who have
watched their world evolve from a small club of male elites into a
yeasty mix of men and women from every continent say that the
balancing act has grown extraordinarily difficult. By Sandra
Blakeslee.
