selectively to his southwest Arkansas roots, as in the 1992
presidential campaign when he wanted to be the ``man from Hope.''
He makes one of those pilgrimages Friday for the dedication of the
home where he lived until he was 4. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   DRUG-CERTIFICATION (Washington) _ Conservative Sen. Phil Gramm
of Texas and liberal Sen. Barbara Boxer of California introduce an
alternative to the annual process whereby the White House certifies
which of some 28 nations are partners in the fight against illegal
narcotics. The process, in effect for 13 years, draws perennial
criticism from lawmakers in both parties. By GARY MARTIN. (Already
filed.)
