</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Entering the GOP presidential
sweepstakes, Elizabeth Dole failed to mention her husband in order
to stress that she is in this alone, running on her own public
service credentials. Nor was he at her side, as a supportive spouse
usually is for such a momentous event. Yet she would not be a
front-runner if her name was Elizabeth Hanford. And it is going to
be a strain to ignore him. So what to do with Bob during her
campaign? By MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed.)
