therapy. Now she's trying to return to work but running into
problems. She needs a completely ergonomically sound workstation,
including a computer table that can adjust to either sitting or
standing height. So far, she's found that employers stop returning
her calls when they learn about her ergonomic needs. What can she
do? Columnist Ilana DeBare has the answer.
</P>
