<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STARWARS-WEB12-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A galaxy of Web sites
 &HT;    By Jeff Houck
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Thousands of unofficial fan Web sites
are up and running, in anticipation of ``Episode I: The Phantom
Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   Here are a few of the main sites that will help even the biggest
``Star Wars'' novice catch up to diehard fans:
</P>
<P>
   http://www.starwars.com _ Think of this official site by
Lucasfilm as the mother ship of all the Web sites. Not only will
you find updates on Episode I, character details, hints of the plot
and an online dictionary of the terms found in the movies, there's
also a behind-the-scenes documentary and a store where you can buy
trinkets.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.theforce.net _ This is the big daddy of the
unofficial fan sites. It gets so much traffic its operators had to
hire a staff to keep it stocked with fresh news and gossip.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.countingdown.com _ Reminiscent of the disciples who
camped out for Grateful Dead tickets, this site caters to those who
wait in front of theaters overnight to be the first to see Phantom.
They can download a clock that counts down the time until the film
opens.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.jedinet.com _ For the filmgoer who wants the film to
be a surprise, this site's is a minefield. Click the wrong link and
you'll trip over a batch of gossip about the plot. The best find
here: home made mini-movies made by fans with miniature ``Star
Wars'' figures.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.starwarz.com _ Plan to skip the film and avoid the
throngs? Or maybe you just can't wait? Check out this site, which
is full of spoilers.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.thx.com _ The ``prequel'' film was recorded with
Lucas' own mind-blowing THX sound. This site helps you find a
theatre nearby that uses the sound system.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.landspeeder.com _ Discussion board, chat rooms and
lots of rumors. Plus, there are good pictures of the new villain,
Darth Maul.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.sirstevesguide.com _ Lots of toy information here,
along with a lineup of the prequel characters.
</P>
<P>
   Access any of these Web sites, plus watch the prequel trailer
and download ``Star Wars'' game demos at Palm Beach Interactive:
www.GoPBI.com/entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
