<P>
   Moved as BC-NOTRE-DAME-GAY-POLICY:COLBERT-NEWAMERICA-NYTSF in
``k'' commentary and ``a'' general news files.
</P>
<P>
   PRESIDENT CLINTON'S CALL FOR CIVIC PARTICIPATION. Bill Clinton
believes that the government should provide conditions and tools to
empower people to meet their own challenges, notes Mark Keam in
KoreAm Journal. But ``I saw that ... the Korean American community
failed to live up to its end of the partnership, like participating
in townhall meetings, even in towns or cities with large KA
populations, or attended White House conferences on issues
important to Korean Americans, or appeared at briefings on the
President's Initiative on Race,'' he writes. ``Isn't it time for
each of us to ask, `What can I do for my country?'
</P>
<P>
   Moved as BC-CIVIC-PARTICIPATION-NEWAMERICA-NYTSF in ``k''
commentary and ``a'' general news files.
</P>
<P>
   ``EXTINCT'' TAINO NATION RECOVERED AND RESTORED. Members of an
Indian Nation thought to be extinct, reclaim their heritage and
celebrate their culture and history. ``I always thought of myself
as Puerto Rican Taino,'' a Nation member told Rick Kearns of
Hispanic magazine. ``And throughout my whole life, when I mentioned
to other Puerto Ricans that I was part Taino, they replied that I
couldn't be. They said the Tainos are extinct ... .'' But the more
she researched, the more she discovered this was not so.
</P>
<P>
   Moved as BC-TAINO-INDIANS-NEWAMERICA-NYTSF in ``a'' general news
file.
</P>
